5:
...and then Sho opened his mouth
and made everyone so mad. We
must've looked like crazy people.
9:
Ooooh... I had no idea that's what
Sho was like at school!
13:
I'm so jealous! I wish I could've gone
to the same school, then I could've
seen how cool he was in person!
18:
Huh... You actually really like him,
don't you?
22:
You bet I do! I love that he's normally
a sloppy person, but he gets
bothered by the little details of
certain things!
25:
He's also really good at beating up
bad guys! Just the other day, he
was the MVP for the job we were on!
30:
Was that the one where you had to
deal with the crime syndicate
recruiting ex-Aegis people?
35:
Yeah! He did amazingly... I'm glad I
got to see everything...
38:
There's just one thing that bothers
me—the more he shows off his good
side, the more popular he'll be with
other girls...
42:
He's already pretty popular with the
girls in Palpebra. They call him the
Soaring Prince, even.
45:
...Neither of you would fall for Sho,
right?
50: Uh... I'm not really into that sort of—
55: No way. Not in a million years.
60:
I also don't have feelings for people
the way you do, Yukariko. At most,
he's an important friend to me.
65:
Is that right? Sorry for doubting you
guys.
69:
I get that he means that much to
you, but I wouldn't be too worried.
Even he wouldn't be flirting with
other people when—
74:
For real? And you're sure it's okay for
me to tag along?
77:
It's more than okay. We'd LOVE to
have you come with us.
81:
U-uhhh... I wouldn't read too much
into that? Sometimes Sho does
things without really thinking about
it!
90:
Sho... Do you like those kinds of
women?
94: L-let's not do anything hasty here!
102:
You've got the wrong idea! They just
wanted to show me to an eatery
that had good food, that's all!
106:
It's okay, Sho. You didn't do anything
wrong.
112:
Sorry, Sho, but I remembered
something I had to do. I'll be right
back.
120:
...You don't think... She's not... Crap.
We should go after her, shouldn't we?
127:
What do you like about Sho? We can
start with the first hundred things on
your list.
133:
You DO have at least a hundred
things you like about him, right? Or
don't you? Otherwise, you'd be the
same as Mom...
142:
Sho! Were you worried about me?
Oh, you...
145:
I promise I'm more than capable of
taking out the trash by myself!
149:
That's a joke, right? You're really
freaking me out right now!
153: ...I don't mind if you like other women.
162:
...Okay, maybe I wasn't being
completely honest.
165:
It's not right to have feelings for
multiple people, but I can hold
myself back if that's what Sho wants.
168:
The thing is... I have to find out how
much these three actually like him.
171:
So what's your answer? You haven't
told me yet. Spit it out. Tell me. Right
now. Are you all...
174:
The right ones for him? More fit than
me?
177:
W-we were just teasing him a little...
It's not like we're actually trying to
date him.
179:
I mean, I like working with him, but
I'm totally not interested in him that
way...
185: Are you happy now? Can we go?
189:
Of course! Sorry for suspecting you
like that!
201:
Unforgivable. Bad girls like you
need to be punished. I'll teach you
real pain, on top of pain, on top of
pain, on top of pain.
204: So that you'll never forget this lesson.
216:
What? That woman really was a
part of the crime syndicate?
220:
Yeah, guess she was trying to get
revenge against Sho since he was
mostly responsible for kicking their
butts.
224:
That should be the last of the
syndicate that got away though,
thanks to Yukariko here!
229:
Should we really stop at arresting
them?
232:
If we don't take care of them now,
they might come back for Sho once
they're released from prison...
237:
Eh, it's fine! We can just beat 'em up
again if they come back for seconds!
248:
That's right... We were meant to be...
Nothing will get in our way!
253: Huh. Is this what romantic love is like?
263:
Oh yeah, about that whole thing
where I cheered you up when we
were kids...
272: Er, no, uh... I hate to say this, but...
276: I'm pretty sure that wasn't me!
